            "id": 129295,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Programs are more fun if they can take input from the outside.</p><p>When we runÂ code, we can include the input to alter the program.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Order",
            "id": 129296,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>The order of the instructions matters. Once we collect input and store it in a variable, we can reuse it.</p><p>Put the lines in the right order to use the collected output in the output statement.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;What's your name?&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"name_input = input()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;Hi, \" /><text value=\"{name_input}\" class=\"subst\" /><text value=\"!&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"27\" endIndex=\"47\" /><option startIndex=\"48\" endIndex=\"75\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"What's your name?\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Mimo\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Hi, Mimo!\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>name_input = input()</code>, followed by <code>print(f\"Hi, {name_input}!\")</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Console",
            "id": 129297,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>To gather input from a user in a Python program, we use the <code>input</code> function. The user's input can then be assigned to a variable.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"user_input = input()\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"13\" endIndex=\"18\" /><option startIndex=\"18\" endIndex=\"19\" /><option startIndex=\"19\" endIndex=\"20\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>input</code>, followed by <code>(</code>, and finally <code>)</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Displaying multiple times",
            "id": 129298,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>After capturing input, we can assign it to a variable and use it just as any other variable.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;What's your name?&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"user_input = input()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;Hi, \" /><text value=\"{user_input}\" class=\"subst\" /><text value=\"!&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"27\" endIndex=\"37\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"What's your name?\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Mimo\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Hi, Mimo!\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>user_input</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Prompt",
            "id": 129551,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We can also add an additional prompt to the <code>input</code> function. The prompt will be displayed in the console.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"user_input = input(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Enter your name: &quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"19\" endIndex=\"38\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Enter your name: \" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>\"Enter your name: \"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Output",
            "id": 129300,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>If we enter an additional prompt, the user will start typing at the same line as the prompt is displayed in the console.</p><p>That's why it's helpful to add a whitespace at the end of the prompt used in the <code>input</code> function.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"user_input = input(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Enter your name: &quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(f\" /><text value=\"&quot;Thanks, {user_input}!&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"Enter your name: Mimo\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Thanks, Mimo!\" /></content></output></code></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Output - Copy",
            "id": 129552,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We can use the <code>input</code> function as many times as we want.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"user_input_1 = input(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Enter a number: &quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"user_input_2 = input(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Enter another number: &quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(user_input_1)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(user_input_2)\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"Enter a number: 100\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Enter another number: 200\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"100\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"200\" /></content></output></code></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Numbers",
            "id": 129553,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>The input is always of type string. If we want to use it as a number, we need to convert it to an integer or float beforehand.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"user_input_1 = input(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Enter a number: &quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"user_input_2 = input(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Enter another number: &quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"number1 = int(user_input_1)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"number2 = int(user_input_2)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"result = number1 + number2\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(f\" /><text value=\"&quot;The sum is {result}&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"Enter a number: 100\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Enter another number: 200\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"The sum is 300\" /></content></output></code></body></html>"
          },
